results.name: a(n) = Product{k|n} k^(n/k); product is over the positive divisors of n.
link: Harry J. Smith, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..200
example: a(6) = 432 = 1^6 * 2^3 * 3^2 * 6^1 because 1, 2, 3 and 6 are the divisors of 6.
mathematica: Table[Times @@ Map[#^(n/#) &, Divisors@ n], {n, 29}] (* _Michael De Vlieger_, Sep 24 2017 *)
program: (PARI) { for (n=1, 200, d=divisors(n); p=1; for (i=2, length(d), k=d[i]; p*=k^(n/k)); write("b066841.txt", n, " ", p) ) } \\ _Harry J. Smith_, Apr 01 2010
